        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 3:01PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Thicket, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kountze, Saratoga, Thicket, Batson, Village Mills, and Honey Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
